## How to Use This Rule

**This rule applies automatically when creating or modifying any versioned documentation file.**

**Agents should:**
1. **Identify file type** (rule/command/standard/checklist)
2. **Use appropriate version format** (X.Y.Z or X.Y)
3. **Determine increment type** (major/minor/patch) based on change
4. **Update version number** in metadata (never in filename)
5. **Update timestamp** with current EST time
6. **Update CHANGELOG.md** if significant change
7. **Validate** using checklist above

**Quick Reference:**
- **Rules:** `X.Y.Z` format in metadata, increment on any change
- **Commands:** `X.Y.Z` format in metadata, increment on behavior/parameter changes
- **Standards:** `X.Y` format in metadata, increment on requirement changes
- **Checklists:** `X.Y` format in metadata, increment on item changes
- **All files:** Version numbers in metadata only, never in filenames

